In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest discusses a range of topics including President Obama's recent use of the "n" word in an interview, the debate over the Confederate flag in South Carolina, the Iran nuclear deal deadline, gun control legislation, the Greek default crisis, and the Pope's encyclical on climate change. Earnest emphasizes the President's stance on these issues and the need for the American public to take action and make their voices heard.